==English==
===Etymology===
Variously from a number of Slavic languages: Bulgarian [[воиводе]], Serbian, Croatian [[vojvoda]], Czech [[vojvoda]], Polish [[wojewoda]], all from a Slavonic base.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/'vɔɪvəʊd/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|voivode|voivodes}}
# a local ruler or official in various parts of central and eastern Europe, especially early semi-independent rulers of Transylvania
# an administrative chief in modern Poland

